What is the output of the following code?

public class Test {
    static int count = 0;
    Test() {
        count++;
    }
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        new Test();
        new Test();
        System.out.println(Test.count);
    }
}

Given the following code, which line will cause a compilation error?

public class Utility {
    int instanceVar = 10;
    static int staticVar = 20;

    void instanceMethod() {
        System.out.println(instanceVar); // Line A
        System.out.println(staticVar);  // Line B
    }

    static void staticMethod() {
        System.out.println(instanceVar); // Line C
        System.out.println(staticVar);  // Line D
    }
}
